deck: Becky Albright was a witness to one of Scarecrows crimes; he attempted to recruit her as his partner in crime
description:
Becky Albright was a witness to one of Scarecrows crimes; when she refused to recant her testimony he began kidnapping her and exposing her to fear toxin in order to discover her greatest fear. Becky appears to have some deformity such as scoliosis or even cerebral palsy and is terrified of how other people view her, a trait that Jonathan Crane shares.

The Scarecrow stopped tormenting her and attempted to recruit her as his "Mistress of Fear" - Ms. Fear (it appears he had developed a crush)

Becky refuses and is saved by Batman who remarks "looks like she is your greatest fear Dr. Crane"

Becky never took on the mantle as mistress of fear despite many fan wanting to see her become the Scarecrow's love interest.
name: Becky Albright: Mistress of Fear

deck: The lead singer of Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets.
description:
Origin

It is unknown how Rocket Head came to be a cyborg; however, he used his singing talents to become the lead singer of Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets.

Creation

Rocket Head was created by Bob Burden.

Major Story Arcs

Battle of the Bands

Rocket Head and his band were headed to a battle of the bands when they came across the Flaming Carrot. With his flight he was able to help the Flaming Carrot and prevented him from falling a large distance. He then fought alongside the Flaming Carrot to bring down a group of mobsters; unfortunately he was poisoned by their leader, Red Dyke, and was unable to participate in the battle of the bands.

Powers & Abilities

Rocket Head is a human head attached to a small rocket. He has the following abilities:

  • Flight - The rocket that Rocket Head is made of enables him to fly through the sky at high speeds.
  • Cybernetic Attachments - Rocket Head has two smaller rockets attached to his main body. He also has a spear-like attachment on the very tip of his main body that he can use to stab foes or to catch falling objects.
name: Rocket Head

team_friends.name: Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets

teams.name: Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets

deck: A foe of Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets. She attempted to sabotage the battle of the bands so that the Dixie Drug Addicts would be the winners.
description:
Origin

The Red Dyke is of an unknown origin; however, she has been raised to hate capitalists and has a history of sabotaging the bourgeoisie.

Creation

The Red Dyke was created by Bob Burden.

Major Story Arcs

Battle of the Bands

The Red Dyke and her crew of mobsters were attending a battle of the bands to make sure the group they supported, the Dixie Drug Addicts, would win the competition. Using her charm and wit she was able to seduce the lead singer of Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets, Rocket Head, and wound up poisoning him to prevent him from singing in the competition. Unfortunately for her she didn't account for the Flaming Carrot who wound up covering for him.

In an attempt to defeat the Flaming Carrot she boarded a strange vehicle known as the Chirotractor, left behind by a group of chiropractors who had a convention earlier that day, and attacked the stage where the band was performing. The Flaming Carrot wound up boarding her vehicle and covered her eyes while she was driving it to prevent her from seeing. This caused her to drive the vehicle into the nearby lake. Her body was never found and it is unknown if she died or escaped.

Powers and Abilities

The Red Dyke has no actual powers; however, she is known for using her charm to seduce others into doing her dirty work for her. She is also the leader of a mob organization.
name: Red Dyke

team_enemies.name: Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets

deck: Bambo was the zombie slave of Garbagemouth. Once Garbagemouth was killed he tried to team up with his killer, the Flaming Carrot; however, Carrot had him thrown in jail for his crimes. Bambo would eventually prove himself to be a useful ally to Carrot and would help him escape several sinister situations!
description:
Origin

Bambo was once a man; however, he was killed in an unknown accident and became a zombie. He teamed up with Garbagemouth and the two of them committed crimes together.

Creation

Bambo was created by Bob Burden for the relaunch of the Flaming Carrot. He appeared in the first issue, Flaming Carrot Comics #1 - Flaming Carrot Goes PC!

Major Story Arcs

Flaming Carrot Goes PC

Bambo was seen fighting alongside Garbagemouth; however, he was easily distracted by the Flaming Carrot's baloney gun. Once Garbagemouth had been killed by the Flaming Carrot he tried to become Flaming Carrot's side-kick, but Flaming Carrot wanted nothing to do with the zombie and had the federal officers arrest him for his crimes.

Bambo didn't stay imprisoned for long however, using his super human strength he busted out of jail, eventually finding the Flaming Carrot. It was lucky for the Flaming Carrot that Bambo arrived, as his being undead made him immune to the weapons of the Pigmies (of which FC was fighting at the time) and Bambo was able to rescue the Flaming Carrot. His actions (and his charm) won the hearts of FC's many girlfriends and they chose to keep him around, despite the fact that FC wanted to bring him back to prison.

Some Days Are Stones

Now a member of the Flaming Carrot crew, Bambo is seen doing simple chores around the house. Due to his drooling issue (likely because he's a zombie) he now has a cup taped to his chin. His relationship with FC's girlfriends progressed to the point where FC worried that they might like Bambo more than they like him!

Bambo is seen again at the home of the Flaming Carrot when a door-to-door salesmen comes knocking. He proves his worth when he attacks the salesmen, sending him running and making his new master, the Flaming Carrot, incredibly pleased. Unfortunately Bambo would goof up after following the Flaming Carrot to his date with Princess Norma Lescaboura, scaring the Princess and causing her to flee. To make up for his error he aided the Flaming Carrot when he took on the Pigmies for a second time, jumping from a helicopter to destroy the massive ear they were constructing out of paste and french bread.

Flaming Carrot and his pals were unable to find Bambo after his bold move, but the epilogue to this story suggests that he wound up obtaining a massive amount of money from an unknown source and cashing it, eventually moving on to a new portion of his life.

Powers & Abilities

Bambo is a zombie and is assumed to have all of the properties of the traditional zombie.
name: Bambo

deck: Garbagemouth is the foul-mouthed foe of the Flaming Carrot. He rides around in a poorly constructed power suit and can fire deadly sharp razor blades.
description:
Origin

It is unknown how or why Garbagemouth is the villain he is but one thing is for certain, he has a strong dislike for the Flaming Carrot and will do anything in his power to stop him.

Creation

Garbagemouth was created by Bob Burden to appear in the relaunch of the Flaming Carrot. He made his debut in Flaming Carrot Comics #1 - Flaming Carrot Goes PC!

Major Story Arcs

Flaming Carrot Goes PC

Garbagemouth appeared alongside his zombie partner, Bambo, attacking the Flaming Carrot. He taunted the Flaming Carrot and his silly weapon, the baloney gun, making remarks about how it'd be impossible to harm someone with it.

Unfortunately for Garbagemouth, Flaming Carrot found a way to make his toy weapon incredibly lethal as he fired an entire tube of baloney into Garbagemouth's mouth, thus killing him. When the authorities were inspecting his body they found that he was so full of baloney that it had begun seeping out of his ears.

Powers & Abilities

Garbagemouth has no powers; however, he is able to fire incredibly sharp razor discs out of the battle suit he wears.
name: Garbagemouth

deck: Jotaro Kujo is the grandson of Joseph Joestar and the main protagonist of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part 3: Stardust Crusaders
description:
In Other Media

Animated

  • Jotaro is the main protagonist in the Stardust Crusaders OVAs, voiced by Abie Hadjitarkhani.
  • Jotaro is again the main protagonist in the anime adaptation of Stardust Crusaders, voiced by Daisuke Ono
  • Daisuke Ono reprises his role in the anime adaptation of Diamond is Unbreakable, voicing the older Jotaro.

Film

  • Jotaro appears in the live-action JoJo's Bizarre Adventure movie, portrayed by Japanese actor Yusuke Iseya. Iseya portrays the older version of Josuke from Part IV: Diamond is Unbreakable, rather than his teenage incarnation from Part III.

Video Games

Jotaro is a playable character in the following games:

  • JoJo's Bizarre Adventure
  • JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Heritage for the Future
  • JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: All-Star Battle
  • JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Eyes of Heaven

deck: Dwight is a young man who somehow has obtained Ant-Man's helmet, allowing him mental control of an army of ants. Dwight will not allow anyone to cross his bridge in Des Moines, Iowa without paying.
description:
History

Dwight first appears in Old Man Logan part 3 (Wolverine # 70) and stops Hawkeye and Wolverine while they are driving East. Dwight operates out of Des Moines, Iowa by controlling a bridge he has named Dwight's Toll, making any who wish to cross pay up under the threat of death. Hawkeye gladly pays.

Abilities

Dwight wields the Ant-Man held, which allows the wearer to mentally control ants. Dwight uses the helmet to control an army of several million ants to coerce those who would like to use his bridge with the threat of violence.

deck: The Tooth Fairy is a Falseblood, the product of a Highborn father from Myst and a human mother.
description:
Origin

Gwendolyn's father is a Highborn from Myst. He was one of the Dark Queen's most loyal warriors. She sent him to Earth to study and learn more about humans. That's when he met a human woman and raped her. Her mother was pregnant with Gwen when the Myst's guardians hunted her father and killed him.

Already hungry while still in the womb, Gwen fed on her mother's bones and chewed her way outside of her mother. Punishing herself by starving herself, her wings wilted away over time.

She must condume a child's first tooth to restore her powers to full strength, but she craves human bones instead.
name: Tooth Fairy

deck: Calista is the queen of the water nymphs from Neverland and Hailey's mother.
description:
Origin

Calista is the queen of the water nymphs in Neverland. Seventeen years ago, she fled Neverland during Pan's reign of evil. For a time, she lived like a human woman on Earth, where she met Harold. She and Harold had a child, Hailey. Calista left Hailey when she was five years old.

Major Story Arcs

Rise of the Water Nymphs

Calista abducts Hailey and takes her to Neverland. She claims the water nymphs are at war with the sirens and decided not to fight them. Instead she wants the water nymphs to relocate to Atlantis and wants to take her daughter with her to keep her safe. In the war against the sirens, Calista is caught off-guard and killed by a siren.
